{
  "stem": "33.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "So some people, you know, did have a lot of decency.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Also, the radios were taken away, so we gave our radio to him.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "He had-- my room was on the second level.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "The rest of the house was on one level.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We had a kitchen, and pantry, and a lot of other things in a semi-basement.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And he got my room on the second level.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And that's where the radio was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And my father was really addicted to listening to the news during the war.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I guess my cousin and I counted once that he was listening to like 18 newscasts one day-- everything from BBC, from the British radio-- in French, German, Hungarian, sometimes even Italian, even though he didn't perfectly understand it.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But from the Romanian and French, he understood enough.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "So for him, for my father, it was a really devastating thing not to have a radio.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And I remember he asked this doctor once, well, what is on the news?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he said it was like the Hungarian news that was going to come.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he said, oh, I'm not listening to that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Come on up, and we can listen to BBC.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So that was before he was taken hostage.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So from then on, like, he were-- they were listening to the BBC.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I mean, this man knew that they lost the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So it was, you know, maybe he was nice anyway.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But he wanted to be friendly.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Anyway, he was a hostage until the ghetto started.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was-- where I'm from, high school graduation is not like you're 18, and you're alive, and you graduate high school.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
